Package: com.stehno.effigy.annotation

[Groovy] Annotation Type Component

    • com.stehno.effigy.annotation.Component

    • Annotation used to denote a property as a one-to-one relationship with the enclosing entity. The one-to-one assocation expressed by a Component is similar to an

      Embedded:
      object; however, this relation data is contained in a separate lookup table, rather than embedded within the same table. The type of the annotated field may be an Entity-annotated class; however, the entity table property as well as any Id, Version annotated fields will be ignored by the Component association functionality.

        • java.lang.String entityColumn()

          The column name of the field used to identify the owning entity in the associated table. If not specified, the default will be the table name of the owning entity suffixed with '_id'.

        • java.lang.String lookupTable()

          The database table used to store the component information. If not specified, the default will be a table named as the embedded type name suffixed with an 's'.

          Default:
          ''
